# Auth & Authorization Implementation Plan
## Contract Intelligence Capstone

### Background
The existing application has:
- **Backend**: FastAPI, Neo4j (Aura cloud), centralized JSON logger ([get_logger](file:///c:/Capstone/contract_agent_capstone/backend/shared/utils/logger.py#45-52)) + [TracingMiddleware](file:///c:/Capstone/contract_agent_capstone/backend/shared/middleware/tracing.py#9-33) with `correlation_id_var`
- **Frontend**: Vite/React/TypeScript, simple hash-router ([useRouter](file:///c:/Capstone/contract_agent_capstone/frontend/src/lib/useRouter.ts#5-17)), no auth context
- **Infrastructure**: Docker Compose with `backend`, [ui](file:///c:/Capstone/contract_agent_capstone/backend/main.py#136-154), `phoenix` services only — **no PostgreSQL service**
- **No existing authentication or authorization** of any kind

This plan adds authentication (Step 1) and RBAC authorization (Step 2) on top of the existing stack while reusing all existing logging, middleware, and dependency injection patterns.

