## Gap Analysis (Additions vs. Original Plan)

| Gap | Resolution |
|---|---|
| `console.log` in frontend is a security risk | **New** `frontend/src/utils/logger.ts` — structured, level-aware frontend logger; no `console.*` anywhere in auth/RBAC code |
| All existing API services use raw `fetch` with **no auth headers** | **New** `frontend/src/services/apiClient.ts` — centralized fetch wrapper that attaches `Authorization: Bearer` + `X-Correlation-ID` on every request |
| 401 responses not handled globally → silent dead requests | `apiClient` intercepts 401 → clears token and fires `AuthContext.logout()` |
| [useRouter](file:///c:/Capstone/contract_agent_capstone/frontend/src/lib/useRouter.ts#5-17) has no `'login'` page type | Extend [PageType](file:///c:/Capstone/contract_agent_capstone/frontend/src/lib/useRouter.ts#3-4) union in [useRouter.ts](file:///c:/Capstone/contract_agent_capstone/frontend/src/lib/useRouter.ts); `AuthContext` calls `navigate('login')` on logout |
| Hardcoded `http://localhost:8000` in [enhancedSearchApi.ts](file:///c:/Capstone/contract_agent_capstone/frontend/src/services/enhancedSearchApi.ts) | All services migrated to use `apiClient`, which reads `import.meta.env.VITE_BACKEND_URL` |
| No database migration tooling (only `create_all`) | Add **Alembic** for version-controlled schema migrations; `create_all` kept only as fallback for dev |
| [JsonFormatter](file:///c:/Capstone/contract_agent_capstone/backend/shared/utils/logger.py#10-31) doesn't emit `user_id` from token | Extend [TracingMiddleware](file:///c:/Capstone/contract_agent_capstone/backend/shared/middleware/tracing.py#9-33) to decode JWT (no exception on failure) and store `user_id` in a new `ContextVar`; [JsonFormatter](file:///c:/Capstone/contract_agent_capstone/backend/shared/utils/logger.py#10-31) emits it automatically |
| Frontend sends no correlation ID | `apiClient.ts` generates a UUID per request and sets `X-Correlation-ID` header, mirroring the backend middleware |

