## Design Principles Applied

| Principle | Where Applied |
|---|---|
| **SRP** | Each auth module has one job: `password.py` → hashing, `jwt_service.py` → tokens, `repository.py` → DB |
| **OCP** | `rbac.py` permission matrix — add new roles without modifying callers |
| **LSP** | Role hierarchy is enforced via set-based permissions, not inheritance |
| **DIP** | `get_current_user`, `get_db` are injected via FastAPI `Depends`, not imported directly |
| **DRY** | `require_role`/`require_permission` are factories — one definition, applied everywhere |
| **Repository Pattern** | `UserRepository` abstracts all DB operations |
| **Strategy Pattern** | `require_permission(perm)` is a configurable dependency strategy per endpoint |
| **Agentic AI Pattern** | Auth context (`user_id`, `role`) is injected into all LLM request tags so agent traces are actor-attributed |

